The Caatinga is the biome that covers most of the area with a semi-arid climate in Northeast Brazil , with approximately 912,529 km 2 distributed in ten states ( Alagoas , Bahia , Ceará , Maranhão , Minas Gerais , Paraíba , Pernambuco , Piauí , Rio Grande do Norte , and Sergipe ), which corresponds to 10.7% of the national territory (
Silva et al. 2018
). The Caatinga has a high level of endemism, with species adapted to the climatic characteristics of low precipitation and humidity (
Silva et al. 2018
). Araújo and Rodrigues (2023), report 65 species belonging to

APAC (Agência Pernambucana de Águas e Clima). 2022. Climatologia [Internet]. [accessed 
10 february 2023
]. Available from https://www.apac.pe.gov.br/193-climatologia/521-climatologia-por-municipio
